column3: Updated: looks like you actually have to go through the main downloads page in order to get the cookie that you need for the download.\n
This is a version of #6236 on the 0.11 branch rather than on master.\n
A second pull request/commit isn't necessary, anything that needs to be backported will be done using your original commit. This should really be sent to the trivial branch either way.\n
Yep, what @fanquake said. #6236 was merged into trivial, so these can both be closed.\n
Trivial? Not sure I know what that means in this context. I don't really think it's trivial, though -- it's instructions fundamental to the OS X build that are nonfunctional.\n
